description: Hunter Biden’s ex wife and his former girlfriend testified Wednesday in a Delaware courtroom about his drug use. His defense asked a FBI special agent about the contents of his infamous laptop.
title: Hunter Biden’s ex wife and his former girlfriend testified in gun trial

description: It’s lawnmower season but some homeowners and others say it’s time to shift from well-trimmed lawns to more environmentally friendly landscaping.
title: The arguments for swapping lawns for more natural landscaping

description: On this week's "My Unsung Hero" from Hidden Brain, when Father Jim Martin's father was dying, a nun, Sister Janice Farnham, took a 5-hour train ride to visit him.
title: A priest recalls what it meant went a nun traveled 5 hours to visit his dying father

description: South Africa is in unchartered political territory as the ruling African National Congress look to other parties to try and shore up its majority after a historic loss of votes in last weeks election.
title: After getting bashed in elections, South Africa's ANC is frantic to form a coalition

description:

title: Gaza's sick and malnourished children die as hospitals collapse from Israel's war

description: The Coast Guard is holding it's strategic wargames at a base in Portsmouth, Va., and climate change is a key adversary.
title: In the Coast Guard's wargames, climate change is now a key adversary

description: The U.S Agency for International Development says that it will be sending $90 million to aid Palestinians in Gaza. The announcement comes amid growing concerns of famine.
title: USAID says it will send $90 million in aid to Gaza

description: Fifty-one years ago, Washington created a daring program to fight poverty. But instead of lifting people, it now traps them in poverty.
title: Supplemental Security Income rules can limit the people the program is meant to help

description: Can the recent Biden’s executive order restricting asylum have a significant long-term impact in reducing the number of illegal crossings in the U.S. Southern border? We’re asking analysts and people following immigration trends. Jasmine Garsd.
title: What to expect from Biden’s border plan

description: Extreme heat warnings are in effect for more than 10 million people in parts of the West. Cities are mobilizing to help the homeless and the elderly while firefighters are on high alert for wildfires.
title: Scorching temperatures prompt excessive heat warnings in southwest U.S.

description: Reenactors and world leaders converge this week for World War II commemorations in Normandy, where Ukraine looms large.
title: Reflections on war past and present permeate D-Day's 80th anniversary

description: Myrna Broncho relies on broadband for medical care after a bad injury on her ranch. She's among millions facing a jump in costs or lost connections if the Affordable Connectivity Program expires.
title: Broadband subsidies for rural Americans are ending, putting telehealth at risk

description: After years of delay, Boeing's Starliner is flying people for the first time with two NASA astronauts heading to the International Space Station. The rocket lifted off from Cape Canaveral, Fla.
title: After long delays, Boeing’s Starliner capsule and crew launch into space

description: Five states have banned ranked choice voting in the last two months, bringing the total number of Republican-leaning states now prohibiting the voting method to 10. Missouri could soon join them.
title: Missouri joins other red states in trying to stamp out ranked choice voting

description: President Biden will deliver a defense of democracy for the 80th anniversary of D-Day. Why rapper Fat Joe is fighting for hospital price transparency.
title: Biden to give D-Day anniversary speech; Fat Joe fights for hospital price transparency

description: Four years ago, President Biden overwhelmingly won among Gen Z and millennial voters, and within that group, voters of color led that support for him. But now — a new poll from the University of Chicago, exclusively obtained by NPR, finds that the coalition may be severely diminished.
title: After backing him in 2020, a new poll shows some young voters are Biden's to lose

description: President Biden's trip to Normandy will commemorate the 80th anniversary of D-Day. But there's also a political subtext to the journey.
title: To mark D-Day, Biden will deliver a defense of democracy that hits on campaign themes

description: The incident is being investigated, though the woman's current condition is unknown. The National Park Service advises visitors to stay at least 25 to 100 yards away from wild animals.
title: An 83-year-old woman is injured after being gored by a bison at Yellowstone park

description: Republican Tim Sheehy won his party’s nomination to run for Montana’s U.S. Senate seat on Tuesday.
title: Tim Sheehy won the Montana GOP primary. November's race may decide Senate control
